    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "About the usage: We talked about that on IRC, and i will find a better way to archive my goal. However, the usage for this PR is simple: Allow per-frame custom properties to be set. Here is an usecase:\r\n![spriteswithpoints](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1322277/24838834/2d7f0a8e-1d50-11e7-8951-ff3d629b8dd9.gif)\r\nThis vehicle for example \"hops\" while moving. The turret has to be reposition for every frame - but should not affect the logic. For the logic part, the turret has to stay at the center to have the same range in all directions. This custom data has to be present on frame level, which is what this PR allows you to do. This PR is an requirement before i can teach the renderer how to correctly handle this information."
  },
